From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Jeongseok (JS) Lee" <jeongseok@meta.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 16:26:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Remove ninja from Python runtime metadata

The conda-forge ninja package provides the executable needed by PyTorch
extension tooling, but it is not the PyPI Python distribution named
"ninja" and therefore cannot satisfy pip check via Python distribution
metadata.

TorchANI does not import ninja at runtime, so keep the executable
dependency in the conda recipe and remove only the Python metadata
dependency from the built wheel.
---
 pyproject.toml | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml
index 526ee18..633827b 100644
--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -21,7 +21,6 @@ dependencies = [
     "typing_extensions>=4.0.0",
     "h5py",
     "tqdm",
-    "ninja",
     "typer",
     "rich",
     "ase",
